   <refnamediv>
       <refname>meanc</refname>
               <refpurpose>mimics gauss function meanc </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>v=meanc(mat)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> mat </term> =    a (n x p) matrix</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> v </term> =    a (p x 1) vector</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function that mimics gauss function meanc: takes the mean of each column of a matrix and stores it in a column. Is equivalent to v=mean(mat,'r')'.

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
x1=ones(7,1);x2=[1:7]';v = meanc([x1 x2])//returns
// v  =//!   1. !//!   4. !
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
